org.safs.staf.service.logging

Class CustomLogFac

  • java.lang.Object
    • org.safs.staf.service.logging.CustomLogFac

  • public class CustomLogFac
extends java.lang.Object
    This class and AbstractSAFSCustomLoggingService provide a sample custom logging service implementation that writes directly to the STAF logs.
    See Also:
    AbstractSAFSCustomLoggingService, SAFSCustomLoggingService, SAFSCustomLoggingService3

    • Constructor Detail

      • CustomLogFac

        public CustomLogFac(java.lang.String name,
            long mode,
            java.lang.String linked,
            HandleInterface h,
            java.lang.String stafLog)
        Creates a CustomLogFac.

        Parameters:
        name - the name of this custom log facility.
        mode - the log mode of this custom log facility.
        linked - the name of the log facility linked to this one.
        h - the STAF handle for interacting with STAF.
        stafLog - the name of the STAF Log service loaded by standard logging service.

      • isModeEnabled

        public boolean isModeEnabled(long mode)
        Tests if the specified log mode is enabled.

        Parameters:
        mode - the mode to test. Must be one of the LOGMODE constants.
        Returns:
        true if mode is enabled; false if not.

      • logMessage

        public com.ibm.staf.STAFResult logMessage(java.lang.String msg,
                                 java.lang.String desc,
                                 int msgType)
        Logs a message to all the enabled logs.

        Parameters:
        msg - the message to log.
        desc - additional description to log.
        msgType - the int identifier of the type of message being logged.
        Returns:
        a STAFResult indicating the result of the operation and whether normal logging is to be bypassed. Normal logging will be bypassed if rc of the return value is STAFResult.Ok and the result buffer is "BYPASS".

      • close

        public void close()
        Closes all logs of this log facility.
